mp4pack. a media collection manager
Lior Galanti lior.galanti@gmail.com

Usage: mp4pack.py [options] [file or directory]

Options:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit

  Operations:
    An operation to preform on files found in the search path.

    -i, --info          Show info.
    -c, --copy          Copy into repository.
    -n, --rename        Rename files to standard names.
    -e, --extract       Extract subtitle and chapter and transcode the
                        extracted streams.
    -T, --tag           Update meta tags.
    -O, --optimize      Optimize file layout.
    -P KIND, --pack=KIND
                        KIND is one of [ mkv ]
    -t KIND, --transcode=KIND
                        KIND is one of [ m4v, mkv, srt, txt, jpg, png, ac3 ]
    -C KIND, --transform=KIND
                        KIND is one of [ m4v ]
    -u KIND, --update=KIND
                        KIND is one of [ srt, png, jpg, txt, m4v ]

  Modifiers:
    -o VOLUME, --volume=VOLUME
                        Output volume [ default: auto detect ]
    -p PROFILE, --profile=PROFILE
                        [ default: auto detect ]
    -f REGEX, --filter=REGEX
                        Regex to filter selected file names
    -w, --overwrite     Overwrite existing files
    -r, --recursive     Recursively process sub directories.
    -v LEVEL, --verbosity=LEVEL
                        Logging verbosity level [ default: info ]
    -d, --debug         Only print commands without executing. Also good for
                        dumping the commands into a text file and editing
                        before execution.
    -q QUANTIZER, --quality=QUANTIZER
                        H.264 transcoding Quantizer.
    -W WIDTH, --pixel-width=WIDTH
                        Max output pixel width [ default: set by profile ]
    -l CODE, --language=CODE
                        Languge code used when undefined. [ default: eng ]
    -U, --update-index  Rebuild index for encountered files.
    -5, --md5           Verify md5 checksum on copy.
    -D, --download      Download if no local copy found

  Subtitle:
    Options for manipulating subtitles.

    --input-rate=RATE   Decoding subtitles frame rate.
    --output-rate=RATE  Encoding subtitles frame rate.
    --time-shift=TIME   Subtitles shift offset in milliseconds.
    --NTSC              Convert PAL to NTSC framerate
    --PAL               Convert NTSC to PAL framerate

  Database:
    Options for maintaining database records.

    --initialize        Run only once to initialize the system.
    --map-show=MAP      Map TV Show name to TVDB ID. format: <id>:<name>
    --refresh-movie=IMDb
                        Refresh the movie entry.
    --refresh-tvshow=NAME
                        Refresh the tv show and episode entries.
    --refresh-person=TMDb
                        Refresh the person entry.
    --choose-movie-poster=MAP
                        Choose tmdb movie poster. Takes IMDb:TMDb
